radiographic_examinations.findings: 1.5 cm hypodense lesion in the liver likely representing a hemangioma; portal venous system patent; air-filled and dilated appendix measuring up to 11 mm with surrounding fat stranding and a small amount of fluid; tiny appendicolith at the base of the appendix; two foci of air lateral to the cecum likely intraluminal; small amount of pelvic free fluid; no evidence of biliary dilatation, hydronephrosis, or retroperitoneal lymphadenopathy.
